Wash and dry all produce. Adjust rack to upper position and place a #baking sheet{} inside
oven. Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Bring 1 1/2 cups water and a @salt{pinch} to a boil in
a #small pot{}. Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch cubes. Trim, then thinly
slice @Scallions{2%unit}, separating greens and whites. Finely dice @Roma Tomato{2%unit}.
Halve @Lime{2%unit}, cut one half into wedges. Pick fronds from @Dill{1/4%ounce}(fronds picked, stems discarded); discard stems.
Finely chop fronds. Finely chop @Cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Core and seed @Poblano Pepper{1%unit},
then thinly slice.

Once water boils, stir @Jasmine Rice{3/4%cup} into #pot{}. Cover, lower heat, and reduce
to a simmer. Cook until tender, about ~{14%minutes} (keep covered off heat until ready
to serve). Meanwhile, in a #large bowl{} toss together tomatoes, scallion whites, and
cilantro. Squeeze in juice from lime half, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Set
aside. Toss potatoes with a large drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{5%teaspoon} and season with
@Fry Seasoning{1%tablespoon}, salt, and pepper.

Remove sheet from oven and place potatoes on one half. Toss @Broccoli Florets{8%ounce}
with a large drizzle of oil and season with salt and pepper; place on other side of
sheet. Roast in oven until crisp, about ~{25%minutes}, tossing halfway.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Pat
@Pork Cutlets{24%ounce} dry with a #paper towel{}; season all over with salt and pepper.
Add to pan; cook to desired doneness, ~{2-4%minutes} per side.

> TIP: Work in batches if not all will fit.

Remove pork from pan; set aside to rest. Rinse and wipe out pan, then place over low
heat. Add @Butter{1%tablespoon}, @Dijon Mustard{2%teaspoon}, @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1%unit},
@Sour Cream{2%tablespoon} (save rest for later), 2 tablespoons water, and 1 teaspoon
dill to pan. Stir to combine. Season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: If sauce is thick, add more water, 1 tsp at a time, until loosened.

Divide potatoes, broccoli, and half the pork between plates. Spoon pan sauce over pork.
Garnish with remaining dill, to taste, and serve.

== Adobo Pork Bowl ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat. Add poblano and cook,
tossing, until softened, ~{3-5%minutes}. Thinly slice remaining pork and add to bowl
with tomato mixture, then add @Adobo Sauce{2%ounce} and cooked poblano. Toss to combine.
Fluff rice with a #fork{} and stir in scallion greens. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice and pork mixture between two #reusable plastic containers{2}. Pack each
with a lime wedge and packet of @Sour Cream{4%tablespoon}. Keep refrigerated. When ready
to eat, microwave rice and pork mixture on high for ~{1-2%minutes}. Squeeze over lime
and sour cream before digging in.